from stacey a ros subject re hockey and the hispanic community in rickc richard casare write you have a hard time sell any sport to a community that ca play it on account of availability or financial reason hockey be pretty much a sport for the white and well off what white ye well off definitely not hockey season ticket owner have the lowest average income of any of the fmy major north american sport and think of where the majority of hockey player come from from a farm out in boondock saskatchewan or weedville albertum when wa the last time you saw a hockey league in the inner city the insurance alone be a big enough barrier the inner city be the only place that be poor i think the biggest barrier to hockey in the inner city be no ice to play on stace rick casare silicon graphic cubfan n shoreline blvd just wait till next year mountain view ca 